  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ 425°F/ Gas 7 </p>\n<p>Top, tail and slice the <strong>carrots</strong> at an angle</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>carrots</strong> to one side of a baking tray, drizzle them with <strong>olive oil</strong> and season them with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>\n<p>Add the <strong>Cumberland</strong> <strong>sausages</strong> to the other side of the tray</p>\n<p>Put the tray in the oven and cook for 25 min or until golden and cooked through</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1488.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1488.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1488.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1488.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1488.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle</p>\n<p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span></strong></p>\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a very low heat</p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced red</strong> <strong>onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 10 min or until softened and caramelised</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1488.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1488.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1488.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1488.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1488.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into rough bite-sized pieces</p>\n<p>Add the<strong> potatoes</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiling water</strong> with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> over a high heat and cook for 10-15 min or until fork-tender</p>\n<p>Once cooked, drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p>\n<p>Reserve the sieve</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1488.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1488.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1488.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1488.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1488.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Re-boil a kettle </p>\n<p>Dissolve 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>beef stock cube</strong> in 300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong>, add the <strong>onion marmalade</strong> and mix until fully combined – this is your <strong>onion gravy stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1488.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1488.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1488.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1488.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1488.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the <strong>onion</strong> is caramelised, add 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and cook for 1 min, stirring until the onions are evenly coated in the flour</p>\n<p>Add the<strong> onion gravy stock</strong>, increase the heat to medium and cook for 10-15 min or until thickened to a gravy-like consistency – this is your <strong>red onion gravy</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1488.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1488.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1488.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1488.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1488.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, re-boil a kettle</p>\n<p>Return the <strong>drained potatoes</strong> to a low heat and add a splash of <strong>milk </strong>and a knob of <strong>butter</strong></p>\n<p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and mash until smooth</p>\n<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Rip the leaves off the <strong>spring</strong> <strong>greens</strong>, discard the tough stalks, then layer the leaves over each other, roll them up &amp; slice into thin strips</span></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1488.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1488.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1488.-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1488.-step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1488.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong> sliced spring greens</strong></span> to the reserved sieve over the sink and pour over the <strong>boiled water</strong> until bright green and wilted</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1488.-step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1488.-step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1488.-step-7-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1488.-step-7-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1488.-step-7-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>sausages</strong> over the <strong>mash</strong> with the <strong>wilted <span class=\"text-highlight\">greens</span></strong> and <strong>roasted carrots</strong> to the side</p>\n<p>Pour over the <strong>red onion gravy</strong></p>\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
